Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp with pilos symbols and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 52, 9. Name Andrikos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0377.29.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1046)
